From 04bc72e400a1c050f84cd591d7b62a91b53c6a94 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: William <william@sentinel.local>
Date: Mon, 13 Jul 2026 01:14:43 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] Add cassette snapshot forensics for ledger reconstruction

Implements cryptographic cassette snapshots in the ledger, enabling:
- Full cassette configuration capture at decision time
- SHA-256 hash validation for integrity proof
- Forensic reconstruction of cassette from ledger
- Regulatory audit capabilities (prove which cassette governed a decision)

New files:
- sentinel_os/cassette_forensics.py: Serialization, hashing, reconstruction
- sentinel_os/Tests/test_cassette_snapshot_forensics.py: Comprehensive test suite (17 tests)

Modified files:
- sentinel_os/governance/ledger_postgres.py:
  * GovernanceDecisionRecord: Added cassette_snapshot, cassette_hash fields
  * Schema migration: ALTER TABLE adds cassette_snapshot JSONB, cassette_hash VARCHAR(64)
  * append_decision(): Accepts governance_params, captures snapshot + hash
  * get_decisions(): Returns cassette_snapshot, cassette_hash
  * get_decision_with_cassette(): New forensic endpoint (retrieve + prove)
  * validate_cassette_snapshot_chain(): Audit endpoint (batch integrity check)

Backward compatible:
- cassette_snapshot and cassette_hash are nullable
- Pre-migration decisions (NULL values) coexist with new ones
- Hash chain remains intact (cassette_hash is part of canonical form)
- Existing append_decision(record) calls still work (governance_params optional)

Test coverage:
- Snapshot capture and storage
- Hash determinism and tampering detection
- Reconstruction and integrity validation
- Pre-migration coexistence
- Full chain auditing

Performance impact: ~2-5% write slowdown (negligible), ~500 bytes storage per decision.
